snippet.textDisplay: 4:46 😱😷

Interesting. This must be an American dodgeball or NFL dodgeball.
I used to play that every day until the age of 12 before junior high. Classes were large so we played 40 vs 40. There was/were persons outside the field. When anyone inside the field fails to receive the ball or gets hit by the ball, the person is ousted and moves to the outfield. The persons outside pass the ball to teammates inside the field or throw the ball to hit anyone inside. That means people inside the field have to catch or dodge the ball thrown from the outside and inside, which is four directions.
